news.title: Sebi to auction 28 properties of five companies to recover investor money
news.para: The properties will be auctioned for a reserve price of Rs 28.66 crore. Ravi Kiran Realty India, Mangalam Agro Products , and Purusattam Infotech Industries are the other companies, whose properties will be auctioned.

news.title: Office demand continues to scale-up in 2024
news.para: At India level, 2024 is likely to see Grade A absorption breach 60 million sq feet for the first time in the office market of the country.

news.title: Norway's wealth fund acquires full ownership of eight US properties for $976.8 million
news.para: "In a period of heightened dislocation in the office sector, we see this as an opportune moment to invest," said Per Loeken, the fund's global co-head of unlisted real estate.

news.title: Residential realty demand, supply growth to remain steady this fiscal
news.para: Demand growth in the last two fiscals was resilient on account of factors such as favourable macroeconomic conditions and the rise in household income levels outpacing the appreciation in housing capital values.

news.title: OYO acquires G6 Hospitality for $525 million
news.para: On September 20, OYO agreed to acquire US-based G6 Hospitality, the parent company of the Motel 6 and Studio 6 brands, in an all-cash transaction.

news.title: Mall vacancy levels down to 8.3% in H1 FY25: Report
news.para: The demand was higher than supply for the third consecutive year; over 3.1 million sq ft retail space leased in H1 2024.

news.title: Developers to launch 253.16 million sq ft of new supply over next few years: Anarock
news.para: Of this total planned supply, just 23% (approx. 57.15 million sq ft) were launched in H1 FY 2025.

news.title: India Cements shares surge 11% after CCI approves acquisition with UltraTech cement
news.para: The stock soared 11 per cent to Rs 376.30 on the BSE. At the NSE, it surged 10.92 per cent to Rs 376.20.

news.title: TVS Emerald buys 12-acre land worth Rs 2,800 crore in Chennai
news.para: The land will have a development potential of 2.5 million square feet and a revenue potential of Rs 2,800 crore, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Pune: Kharadi property cards of flat owners to be uploaded on Mahabhumi portal
news.para: The department had decided to do away with 7/12 extracts in cities where the property survey has been completed and property cards issued. The project aims at curbing frauds in the real estate sector.

news.title: Mumbai: Redevelopment of Nargis Dutt Nagar to attract Rs 10,000 crore investment
news.para: The sale component potential of about 10 lakh sq ft itself is worth around Rs 10,000 crore, said property market sources.

news.title: GST charges will increase home prices by 10%: Credai Pune
news.para: FSI determines the maximum permitted floor area that can be developed on a plot of land and controls construction density in that area.

news.title: Noida: Homebuyers of Jaypee Infratech approaches NCLT over construction delays
news.para: According to the approved resolution plan — passed by NCLAT in May this year — Suraksha was supposed to resume construction of flats within 90 days.

news.title: NCLT approves Raymond's plan to demerge its real estate business
news.para: Raymond Ltd, the demerged company, will transfer its real estate assets and operations to Raymond Realty Limited, the resulting company, effective from April 1, 2025.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government set to allocate 2,000 more acres of land to Sri City
news.para: Andhra Pradesh govt allocated 8000 acres of land to Sri City near Satyavedu and Varadaiahpalem mandals in Tirupati district at the time of its inception in 2008.

news.title: About 180 illegal structures demolished in Kanpur
news.para: The operation commenced from Bhairav Ghat crossing to KD Palace via Gwaltoli area. According to official communication, four trucks of household possessions belonging to the encroachers were confiscated.

news.title: Allahabad HC orders vigilance probe into Himalayan cooperative housing society fraud
news.para: The court directed the vigilance department to present the investigation report before it on Jan 20, while taking action against the employees of the society and LDA.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to conduct an inspection at Aryabhata Tech Park
news.para: At the ATP, spread over 26 acres, 10 companies were allotted land in two phases for the development of IT-BT industries. The HDMC decided to constitute a house panel to verify the ATP.

news.title: Unfinished housing projects to cost Ahmedabad civic body Rs 46 crore more
news.para: The Housing Improvement and Urban Poor Housing Scheme Committee endorsed two proposals on Friday that will cost the AMC Rs 45.94 crore.

news.title: Nashik civic body mops up Rs 40 crore property tax via amnesty scheme since Oct 1
news.para: In the last three weeks, NMC raked in Rs13 crore via the scheme. The amount Rs 600 crore includes Rs 268 crore as the penalty.
